From: jeremy@myfacetwittertube.com
Subject: [PATCH] abliterate: handle empty whitened-SVD result at early layers

When extracting whitened-SVD directions from very early layers (e.g. layer 0),
the SVD frequently returns an empty `result.directions` tensor because no
significant variance is concentrated along the harmful-vs-harmless contrast
this early in the residual stream. The original code unconditionally indexes
`result.directions[0]`, which raises IndexError and aborts the entire
abliteration pipeline.

This was reproducible on Gemma-4-E2B-it (DENSE+REASONING; arch profile bumps
n_directions to 12 → small-model cap to 2 → still hits the multi-direction
SVD path) and is the load-bearing failure for any whitened-SVD method on
small models.

Fix: detect the empty result and skip the layer (leaving its entry unset
in self.refusal_directions, which downstream code already treats as "no
direction at this layer").

Apply with: cd /path/to/OBLITERATUS && git apply 0001-whitened-svd-empty-result.patch

---
 obliteratus/abliterate.py | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/obliteratus/abliterate.py b/obliteratus/abliterate.py
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/obliteratus/abliterate.py
+++ b/obliteratus/abliterate.py
@@ -1635,11 +1635,20 @@ class AbliterationPipeline:
             elif whitened_extractor is not None:
                 # Whitened SVD: normalize by harmless covariance first
                 result = whitened_extractor.extract(
                     self._harmful_acts[idx],
                     self._harmless_acts[idx],
                     n_directions=n_dirs,
                     layer_idx=idx,
                 )
+                if result.directions.shape[0] == 0:
+                    # Whitened SVD found no significant direction at this layer
+                    # (typical at very early layers where refusal hasn't formed
+                    # yet). Skip — leave self.refusal_directions[idx] unset so
+                    # downstream code treats this layer as no-op.
+                    if idx < 5 or idx == n_layers - 1:
+                        self.log(
+                            f"  layer {idx}: whitened SVD returned empty (no significant direction); skipping"
+                        )
+                    continue
                 self.refusal_subspaces[idx] = result.directions
                 self.refusal_directions[idx] = result.directions[0]
                 norms[idx] = result.singular_values.sum().item()
